                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13114775" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 26 Sep 2011 16:50:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Should also then change the next line from&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        if (sources.size() == 1)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;to&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        if (sources.size() &amp;lt;= 1)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1 w/ that&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13115289" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 27 Sep 2011 07:34:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hum, I don&apos;t think that works because both OneToOne and TrivialOneToOne constructors do sources.get(0), so that should stay a == 1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The initial idea was to use the manyToOne that works fine will an empty list of sources, but attaching an alternative v2 that adds a simple EmptyIterator for the empty case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13115453" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 27 Sep 2011 12:49:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13115454" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 27 Sep 2011 12:50:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;TBH worrying about the empty case is probably premature optimization, so I&apos;m fine w/ committing either one.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13115473" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 27 Sep 2011 13:16:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree this is premature optimization, I attached the second one as an alternative to consider. Committed the first one.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
